            <entry xml:id="Lfd4f626be8bc45ea883867cd59e9efc0" n="2">
               <form>
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሆሄ</foreign>
               </form>
               <sense xml:lang="la" source="#dillmann" xml:id="Dmain"> <gramGrp> <pos expand="not found">subst.</pos> </gramGrp> <lbl expand="pluralis">Pl.</lbl> <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሆህያት፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> sonus </quote>
                        </cit>et <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> litera alphabeti </quote>
                        </cit>, <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> elementum </quote>
                        </cit>. Plur. potissimum in usu fuit: etiam ubi singularem expectaveris, nonnunquam pluralem invenies, ut <foreign xml:lang="gez">በከመ፡ ሆህያተ፡ አልፋ፡ ትከውን፡ ኀበ፡ ኵሎሙ፡ ሆህያት፡</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="grc">ὥσπερ ἐπὶ τῶν στοιχείων τὸ πᾶν τὸ ἄλφα συνέχει</foreign> <ref cRef="Chrys. ho." loc="9.">Chrys. ho. 9.</ref> Quare haud mirum videtur, quod Abyssini inferioris aetatis, singularis formam veram ignorantes, pro <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሆሄ፡</foreign> (<ref cRef="F.N." loc=" in Proleg.">F.N.  in Proleg.</ref>) formam <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኆኅት፡</foreign> exscribere solent, ut <ref cRef="Sx. Teq." loc="18 ">Sx. Teq. 18 </ref>(ter); <ref cRef="Cod. Mus. Brit. LVII, 2" loc=" str. 1">Cod. Mus. Brit. LVII, 2  str. 1</ref> (in <ref cRef="Catal." loc="54,">Catal. p. 54,</ref> ubi <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> initium </quote>
                        </cit>male pro <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> litera </quote>
                        </cit>versum est), quasi nomen ad <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኆኅት፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> janua </quote>
                        </cit>referendum et <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> elementum </quote>
                        </cit>a <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> fenestellis </quote>
                        </cit>vel <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> laterculis </quote>
                        </cit>tabularum syllabarii Aethiopici dictum sit. Sed etymon a Ludolfo propositum magis placet, sive <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሆሄ፡</foreign> sonuisse, sive e <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሆ</foreign> VIIi et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሄ</foreign> Vi ordinis compositum dicas. Exempla: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ለለማኅደር፡ ስምዮሙ፡ በሆህያተ፡ ጽርእ፡ እምአልፋ፡ ወቤጣ፡ ወጋማ፡</foreign> <cit type="translation" xml:lang="la">
                            <quote> et singulas cellulas nomines literis alphabeti Graeci </quote>
                        </cit> <foreign xml:lang="grc">α</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">β</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">γ</foreign> <ref cRef="Reg. Pach." loc="">Reg. Pach. </ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሆህያት፡</foreign> vel <foreign xml:lang="gez">ሆህያተ፡ ፊደል፡</foreign> <foreign xml:lang="grc">τὰ στοιχεῖα</foreign> saepius in <ref cRef="Chrys. ho." loc="8 ">Chrys. ho. 8 </ref>et <ref cRef="Chrys. ho." loc="9">Chrys. ho. 9</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">እስመ፡ ሆህያተ፡ ቤት፡ ወዋዌ፡ ፩ ውእቱ፡</foreign> (sive: praepositio <foreign xml:lang="gez">በ፡</foreign> et <foreign xml:lang="gez">ውስተ፡</foreign> idem significant) <ref cRef="Chrys. ho." loc="1">Chrys. ho. 1</ref>; <foreign xml:lang="gez">ይኩን፡ ከመ፡ ዘይሜህር፡ ጽሒፈ፤ ቅድመ፡ ውእቱ፡ ይጽሕፍ፡ ሆህያተ፡</foreign> (v. <foreign xml:lang="gez">ፊደላተ፡</foreign>) <foreign xml:lang="gez">ወምዕራፋተ፡ በእዴሁ፤ ካዕበ፡ ይኤዝዝ፡ ለንኡስ፡ ዘይትሜሀር፡ ከመ፡ ይጽሐፍ፡ ከማሁ፡ በእዴሁ፡</foreign> <ref cRef="F.M." loc=" 2,11">F.M.  2,11</ref>; <ref cRef="Kedr f." loc="52">Kedr f. 52</ref>; al. </sense>
               
